comment.editorialComment: It’s normal to see values in this sector drop by around -2.0% during December. However, last year saw an overall movement of nearly double that and this we believe was driven in part by the fact that the market was strong for longer than we had anticipated and suddenly at the end of the year there was a balancing of the numbers. This year is looking very similar with strength and momentum in the used market carrying on for longer than we expected and this has been holding values up for some time. There comes a point though, where values have to move and December always seems to be the time that this happens. By the middle of November values had moved back by just over -2.0% and we believe there will be further movements of up to -1.0% between now and the beginning of December.

Values in this sector fell quite heavily last year as we went through January. Some were saying that this was due to the large number of pre-reg cars that were still in the market from the year before and others felt that it was just normal trading for the month as dealers took advantage of increased footfall to help clear the decks of overage stock. Either way, we did see a bigger percentage drop than we have done in previous years and our view is that this may well happen again this year. With this in mind, our expectation is that values are likely to drop by -2.0% to -2.5% which could be 0.5% more than the rest of the market.

After several years of rising values during February, last year saw a fundamental change to that pattern and overall values dropped by just under 1.0% as we progressed through the month of February. We expect that this was due to higher than normal volumes in the market which had been carried into the New Year and many vendors were in a position where they needed to clear the decks before the next surge in volume on the back of the March plate change. This led to a change in the supply and demand position and inevitably, values fell as a result. This year could see a similar pattern and we wouldn’t be at all surprised to see values moving back by around -0.5% during the course of the month.
